## ğŸ“Œ Overview  
The **Daily Habits Analytics Dashboard** is a complete analytical system built using **Google Sheets & Excel** to track personal productivity habits across multiple time periods.  
This dashboard converts simple daily inputs into **weekly, monthly, and yearly performance insights**, making it a real-world example of data analytics applied to personal behavior tracking.

This project demonstrates essential Data Analyst skills including:  
- Data cleaning  
- Time-series analysis  
- KPI tracking  
- Dashboard creation  
- Automated insights  
- Trend visualization  
- Continuous data updating  

---

## ğŸ¯ Project Goals  
The goal of this project is to:  
- Measure habit consistency over time  
- Identify performance patterns across days, weeks, and months  
- Visualize productivity trends  
- Highlight areas of improvement  
- Build a long-term data-driven personal development dashboard (till Dec 2026)

---

## ğŸ§  Features  
### **1. Daily Tracking**  
- Checkboxes for each habit  
- Auto-calculation of daily completion %  
- Visual distribution using donut charts  

### **2. Weekly Analysis**  
- Week-by-week performance score  
- KPIs: Best Week, Lowest Week, Average Week  
- Trend line for weekly improvement  
- Automatic â€œNeeds Attention / On Trackâ€ insights  

### **3. Monthly Analytics**  
- Month-wise completion trends  
- Comparison charts  
- Summary of total habit performance  
- Automated formula-based reports  
- Works for all months up to **Dec 2026**

### **4. Yearly Dashboard**  
- Overall productivity trends  
- Consistency %  
- High-level KPIs  
- Line charts + bar charts for insights  

### **5. Automated Insights**  
Custom logic highlights:  
- âš ï¸ Low-performing weeks  
